      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#333333] mb-4">
        Move-Out Cleaning Throughout <span class="gold-gradient">The Shoals</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Serving Tuscumbia and the entire Quad Cities
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        {neighborhoods.map((neighborhood) => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 text-center">
            <Icon name="map-marker-alt" class="w-5 h-5 text-[#FFA985] mr-2" />
            <span class="text-gray-700 font-medium">{neighborhood}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Get Your Deposit Back -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50 px-6">
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#333333] mb-8">
          How We Help You <span class="gold-gradient">Get Your Deposit Back</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
          <p class="mb-6">
            Tuscumbia landlords and property managers know exactly where to look during move-out inspections—inside the oven and refrigerator, cabinet interiors, window tracks, baseboards, bathroom grout, and light fixtures tenants often forget.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            Our move-out cleaning addresses every inspection checkpoint. We clean inside all appliances, detail baseboards and window tracks, scrub bathroom tile and grout, wipe down all cabinet interiors, and ensure every surface meets inspection standards.
          </p>
          <p>
            Professional cleaning often costs less than losing your security deposit—and gives you documented proof that you left the property in excellent condition.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local Expert Guide -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#333333] mb-4">
        Tuscumbia Move-Out Cleaning: <span class="gold-gradient">A Local Expert Guide</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="section-divider mb-10"></div>
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-6">
        <p>
          The Quad Cities rental market — Tuscumbia, Sheffield, Muscle Shoals, and Florence — operates on rhythms distinct from larger metro areas. Rental turnover here is heavily influenced by the University of North Alabama student cycle, with a significant wave of move-outs each May and August as students complete semesters and relocate. That same cycle drives another wave of move-ins, meaning Colbert County and Lauderdale County landlords are often managing multiple unit transitions simultaneously during peak periods. The Valley Clean Team has structured our move-out cleaning capacity to absorb that demand, with same-week availability even during the busiest transition windows. When your lease end date falls in early May or late July, we're ready.
        </p>
        <p>
          Alabama landlord-tenant law gives property managers 35 days from your move-out date to return your security deposit or provide a written itemization of deductions. That sounds like ample time, but the inspection typically happens within the first week — meaning your deposit fate is often determined before you've fully settled into your new place. Understanding that timeline is why professional cleaning at move-out matters so much more than a personal scrub-down. When a landlord or property manager walks through a vacant unit and finds it professionally cleaned, the inspection dynamic shifts entirely. There's no list being quietly assembled while you're standing in another room. The evidence argues for deposit return, not against it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Shoals-area property managers have seen every move-out condition imaginable, and experienced ones know exactly where tenants cut corners. The oven interior is almost always inadequately cleaned by residents — baked-on grease and carbonized food residue require specific products and technique, not just a sponge and patience. Refrigerator coil access panels, the space behind the toilet, window tracks that collect years of debris, and the rubber gasket around dishwasher doors are consistently missed. Bathroom grout — particularly in older Tuscumbia properties that haven't been renovated — often carries discoloration that requires sustained chemical treatment, not surface scrubbing. Our move-out checklist addresses all of these specifically because we've learned through hundreds of Shoals-area cleans exactly what local inspectors look for.
        </p>
        <p>
          The housing stock across the Quad Cities spans a remarkable range of ages and conditions. Tuscumbia has blocks of 1920s and 1930s bungalows with original hardwood floors, plaster walls, and period fixtures that require different cleaning approaches than modern construction. Sheffield offers a mix of post-war ranches and newer developments. Muscle Shoals has a concentration of mid-century homes in established neighborhoods alongside newer subdivisions near the waterway. Florence spans everything from historic downtown apartments to modern single-family rentals. Each property type presents different move-out challenges: hardwood floors show scuffs and heel marks that need specific treatment; older tile grout holds stains differently than newer installations; plaster walls show handprints and scuffs more visibly than modern drywall. We calibrate our approach to the specific property, not a generic checklist.
        </p>
        <p>
          One of the most common mistakes Tuscumbia tenants make at move-out is underestimating the threshold for "clean enough." What passes inspection in one market might not in another, and Shoals-area landlords who've managed properties for decades have exacting standards — particularly for rentals in higher-demand neighborhoods near downtown Tuscumbia or the Colbert County waterways. The test isn't whether the property looks clean to you after you've spent three days packing and hauling boxes. The test is whether it looks clean to someone who doesn't have emotional investment in the space, who is evaluating it with fresh eyes and a financial stake in finding deductions. Professional cleaning removes that variable entirely: your landlord sees the result of trained professionals, not exhausted tenants doing their best.
        </p>
        <p>
          We frequently coordinate both the move-out clean at your departing rental and the move-in clean at your new home — whether that's within Tuscumbia, elsewhere in the Shoals, or a relocation outside the area. For tenants transitioning between units, having one cleaning company handle both removes a significant logistical burden. We schedule the move-out clean for your final day of access to the old property and the move-in clean for before your belongings arrive at the new one, so you're never living in a space that feels like someone else's home. The two-clean coordination is especially valuable for Tuscumbia renters moving to Florence or Muscle Shoals, where the distances are short but the scheduling overlap can be tight during peak moving season.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQs -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-[#333333] mb-4">
        Frequently Asked <span class="gold-gradient">Questions</span>
      </h2>
